cs.NA, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.MS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper focuses on the numerical resolution of the wave equation using a numerical scheme, and discusses the introduction of method errors and round-off errors. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper uses formal methods and theorem proving to verify the correctness of a C program. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the annotation of a C program to specify errors, and the use of Frama-C to generate theorems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the verification of a software program using formal methods and theorem proving. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper discusses the implementation and verification of a numerical scheme for the resolution of the wave equation.
